<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1584,2043]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<bibRefCitation author="Blackburn, T." box="[199,399,1728,1755]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="173 - 203" refId="ref24884" refString="Blackburn, T. (1911) Further notes on Australian Coleoptera, with descriptions of new genera and species. No. XLI. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 35, 173 - 203." type="journal article" year="1911">Blackburn (1911)</bibRefCitation>
did not define the type series, seeing an unknown number of males (vide Articles 73.1.2, 72.1.1), but he said that the “Type” was in SAM and it was listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lea, A. M." box="[914,1037,1765,1791]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref25947" refString="Lea, A. M. (1912) The late Rev. Canon Thomas Blackburn, B. A., and his entomological work. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 36, v-xl." type="book" year="1912">Lea (1912)</bibRefCitation>
as such. 
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[1139,1301,1764,1791]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A." pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref25821" refString="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1992) Melolonthinae. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea. Vol. 9. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 174 - 358." type="book" year="1992">Houston &amp; Weir (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, L. J. &amp; Allsopp, P. G." box="[347,621,1800,1827]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="377 - 409" refId="ref26403" refString="Miller, L. J. &amp; Allsopp, P. G. (2000) Identification of Australian canegrubs (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthini). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 14, 377 - 409. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IT 98019" type="journal article" year="2000">Miller &amp; Allsopp (2000)</bibRefCitation>
all referred to a male “ 
<typeStatus box="[877,980,1800,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">holotype</typeStatus>
” in SAM, but none provided any discussion as to why they considered that 
<bibRefCitation author="Blackburn, T." box="[562,760,1836,1863]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="173 - 203" refId="ref24884" refString="Blackburn, T. (1911) Further notes on Australian Coleoptera, with descriptions of new genera and species. No. XLI. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 35, 173 - 203." type="journal article" year="1911">Blackburn (1911)</bibRefCitation>
might have had only one specimen. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[1219,1381,1836,1863]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton (1978)</bibRefCitation>
provided no discussion, did not label any specimen in ZMB and did not correctly state the collection data on the specimen label, I considered that his mention of a 
<typeStatus box="[664,762,1908,1934]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">holotype</typeStatus>
does not constitute a valid 
<typeStatus box="[1073,1176,1908,1934]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A." box="[151,421,1944,1971]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" refId="ref25821" refString="Houston, W. W. K. &amp; Weir, T. A. (1992) Melolonthinae. In: Houston, W. W. K. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Coleoptera: Scarabaeoidea. Vol. 9. Australian Government Publishing Service, Canberra, pp. 174 - 358." type="book" year="1992">Houston &amp; Weir (1992)</bibRefCitation>
cited the SAM register number I.4526 that fixes a particular specimen and is a 
<typeStatus box="[1334,1437,1944,1970]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation by an incorrect reference to a 
<typeStatus box="[622,720,1980,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">holotype</typeStatus>
(vide Article 74.5).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1584,2043]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,150,249]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
The type locality was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blackburn, T." box="[541,736,2016,2043]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" pagination="173 - 203" refId="ref24884" refString="Blackburn, T. (1911) Further notes on Australian Coleoptera, with descriptions of new genera and species. No. XLI. Transactions of the Royal Society of South Australia, 35, 173 - 203." type="journal article" year="1911">Blackburn (1911)</bibRefCitation>
as “ 
<collectingRegion box="[780,958,2016,2042]" country="Australia" name="South Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">South Australia</collectingRegion>
” and on the label as “Balhannah” [
<geoCoordinate box="[1337,1432,2017,2043]" degrees="34.98" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" precision="555" value="-34.98">34.98°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,262,150,177]" degrees="138.82" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" precision="555" value="138.82">138.82°E</geoCoordinate>
], about 
<quantity box="[354,427,151,177]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" unit="km" value="30.0">30 km</quantity>
south-east of Adelaide; it does not accord with the known distribution of the species in northeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[296,494,187,213]" country="Australia" name="New South Wales" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">New South Wales</collectingRegion>
and southeastern 
<collectingRegion box="[694,826,187,213]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Britton, E. B." box="[840,986,187,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="1 - 150" refId="ref25258" refString="Britton, E. B. (1978) A revision of the Australian chafers (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Vol. 2. Tribe Melolonthini. Australian Journal of Zoology, Supplementary Series, 60, 1 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / AJZS 060" type="journal article" year="1978">Britton 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Allsopp, P. G." box="[996,1164,187,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="311 - 312" refId="ref24265" refString="Allsopp, P. G. (1993 b) Antitrogus planiceps (Blackburn) (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae) identified as damaging Australian sugarcane. Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 32, 311 - 312. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1440 - 6055.1993. tb 00592. x" type="journal article" year="1993">Allsopp 1993b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Allsopp, P. G." box="[1174,1233,187,213]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="159 - 178" refId="ref24325" refString="Allsopp, P. G. (2003) Synopsis of Antitrogus Burmeister (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae). Australian Journal of Entomology, 42, 159 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1440 - 6055.2003.00340. x" type="journal article" year="2003">2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, L. J. &amp; Allsopp, P. G." pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="377 - 409" refId="ref26403" refString="Miller, L. J. &amp; Allsopp, P. G. (2000) Identification of Australian canegrubs (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Melolonthini). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 14, 377 - 409. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IT 98019" type="journal article" year="2000">Miller &amp; Allsopp 2000</bibRefCitation>
). Perhaps, this is why ‘South Australia’ is crossed out on one of the labels.
</paragraph>
